title: Man killed in Orlando mass shooting identified
content:
ORLANDO, Fla. —
One person was killed and five others were wounded Saturday night when shots were fired at an apartment complex in Parramore.
Orlando police said a car drove by about 9:30 p.m. and opened fire on a group of people standing outside the complex in the 1100 block of Conley Street.
Gino Nicolas, 24, was pronounced dead at Orlando Regional Medical Center. A woman suffered life-threatening injuries and remains in critical condition.
Friends and family of Nicolas said he graduated from Florida State University two years ago and worked for the city.

Four other people injured are expected to survive. They have been identified as Cordarius Williams, 24, Daquan Lundy, 23, Ricky Harrison Jr., 23, and Wendell Edwards Jr., 22.
Police said the intended target of the shooting is unknown and no suspect information is available at this time.
Police are asking anyone who saw the car involved or knows something about the shooting to contact them or call Crimeline at 1-800-423-TIPS.
